message:
{{#is_alert}}
@pagerduty-NeuroQuest-Backend

**Device-signature enforcement is rejecting real (active) installs.**

More than the warning/critical threshold of `device_signature:missing|invalid|id_mismatch` rejections from device-aware clients (`@extra.active_install:true`) fired in the last 15 minutes. The normal baseline is ~0 — a spike means a change has started wrongly locking legitimate members out of the per-:id app-user endpoints.

**EMERGENCY ROLLBACK (do this first, it does not require a redeploy):**
1. Set the secret `DEVICE_AUTH_SOFT_MODE=1` on the `api-server` deployment. This puts `requireDeviceSignature` back into verify-and-log mode (it still records every verdict but rejects nothing), so members stop getting 401s immediately.
2. Confirm recovery: this monitor should recover within ~15m as the active-install rejection count drops back toward 0.
3. Then investigate the regression (recent deploy to `artifacts/api-server/src/lib/deviceAuth.ts` or the mobile signer in `artifacts/neuro-quest-mobile/lib/userAuth.ts`) before removing `DEVICE_AUTH_SOFT_MODE` to re-enable enforcement.

Note: `requireDeviceSignatureStrict` (GDPR export/erasure) and `requireUserOrDevice` (IAP entitlements) intentionally IGNORE the soft-mode flag and keep hard-rejecting — soft mode only relaxes the general app-user gate.
{{/is_alert}}
{{#is_recovery}}
Device-signature active-install rejection rate is back below threshold.
